column1: Ehrlich Listens to Rage Against the Machine While Having Sex
column4:
RE: SPACE COMBAT

So I was playing "Call of Duty: Ghosts" with my brother once, and they had this bit about the space station where you have dudes in a firefight in space. Awesome, right? And everyone is rocking these IAR/SAW type automatic weapons, nominally chambered in 5.56 and 7.62. It occurs to me that these are basically the worst possible weapons for a gunfight in zero gravity, zero atmosphere. The thrust generated by the ballistic collision in sport-type firearms would literally send the shooter tumbling over backwards, and the compound effects of repeat shots would mean you'd just have a bunch of dudes spinning around shooting wildly.

I think the best firearm for fighting in space would be a lightweight .22LR.

This is what engineering does to your brain. No fantasy. No fun. Just solutions.

@Shane Green  if no one has any word for you and you don't know, here's what I remember-

1) gang plank- only way to get on the ship. A walkway type thing. Walk ~halfway up, stop, turn and face national ensign. IIRC it is at the stern in port. Salute ensign. Continue up gang plank.
2) OOD- find the dude in whites standing at a podium and looking bored. Walk up to him smartly, come to attention, and salute, displaying orders to the ship and ID in free hand. Render greeting and say something like "MIDN 3/C Shane Green requesting permission to board." He'll scribble something if he feels like it and then probably welcome you and tell you where to go.
3) Go where he tells you to.
4) Get lost on the way. Ask pissed-off looking where the place you're looking for. Don't forget to call him by the wrong rate. They love that.
5) Get where you're supposed to (decent chance it's the captain's hatch.) from there, you freestyle it based on what they tell you.
6) ???
7) Profit.
